      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIGHTY MISS (7) has some solid form under her belt and proved too strong last time to win by 0.8 lengths at Geelong in a handy 22.55 beating Black Nevera. Form from her last run is proving to be solid. The hardest to beat again. FIRE UP MARK (6) charged out of the boxes with a strong early sectional but swamped late when a close up fourth (26.02) at Ballarat over 450m. Form from his last run is proving strong. In the mix. KENZIE KID (2) turned in a better effort at Warragul last start, finishing second behind Bull Durham (23.03) in a Grade 4/5. Settled off speed and worked to the line nicely. Has performed well from this box with a win and three minor placings to her name from five starts. Expected to be in the finish again. FIELD OF ANGELS (4) is worth a look over a shorter journey this time.",
